13. 
<taxonomicName LSID="91F1083C-905A-5E3C-8E5F-1C0C1F7390AD" authority="(Phil.) I. M. Johnst., Contr. Gray Herb. 78: 55. 1927." authorityName="(Phil.) I. M. Johnst., Contr. Gray Herb. 78: 55. 1927." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cryptantha glomerulifera" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glomerulifera">Cryptantha glomerulifera (Phil.) I.M. Johnst., Contr. Gray Herb. 78: 55. 1927.</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cryptantha glomerulifera" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glomerulifera">Cryptantha glomerulifera</taxonomicName>
≡ 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eritrichium glomeruliferum" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glomeruliferum">Eritrichium glomeruliferum</taxonomicName>
Phil., Anales Univ. Chile 90: 521. 1895. Type: Chile. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Región">Region</normalizedToken>
de Coquimbo: Las Mollacas, Cordillera de Illapel, 1888, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">F. Philippi s.n.</emphasis>
(first-step lectotype, designated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">Johnston 1927</bibRefCitation>
, pg. 56: SGO; second-step lectotype, designated here: SGO [SGO000004088 digital image!]; isolectotypes: GH [GH00096394 digital image!], SGO [SGO000004089 digital image!]).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
The protologue of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eritrichium glomeruliferum" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glomeruliferum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Eritrichium glomeruliferum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5354/0717-8883.2012.20872" author="Philippi, RA" journalOrPublisher="Anales de la Universidad de Chile" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="511 - 566" refId="B39" refString="Philippi, RA, 1895. Plantas nuevas chilenas de las familias que corresponden al tomo IV de la obra de Gay: (continuacion). Anales de la Universidad de Chile 90: 511 - 566, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5354/0717-8883.2012.20872" title="Plantas nuevas chilenas de las familias que corresponden al tomo IV de la obra de Gay: (continuacion)." url="https://doi.org/10.5354/0717-8883.2012.20872" volume="90" year="1895">Philippi 1895</bibRefCitation>
) includes a direct reference to a collection made by F. Philippi in Las Mollacas, Chile. Two specimens in agreement with the protologue as referred to by R. A. Philippi are found at SGO. 
<bibRefCitation author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">Johnston (1927)</bibRefCitation>
referred to a specimen kept at SGO as the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“type”">&quot;type&quot;</normalizedToken>
of the species name, while 
<bibRefCitation author="Perez-Moreau, RL" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" refId="B30" refString="Perez-Moreau, RL, 1976. Revision del genero Cryptantha en la Argentina (Boraginaceae). Darwiniana 20(1/2): 155-188." title="Revision del genero Cryptantha en la Argentina (Boraginaceae). Darwiniana 20 (1 / 2): 155 - 188." year="1976">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pérez-Moreau">Perez-Moreau</normalizedToken>
(1976)
</bibRefCitation>
later discussed this name and its original material, stating &quot;Chile. Coquimbo, Las Mollacas, Cordillera de Illapel, s/c, 1-1888 (tipo de 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. glomeruliferum" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" rank="species" species="glomeruliferum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">E. glomeruliferum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, SGO)&quot;. However, the statements made by the authors are insufficiently precise since it cannot be ascertained to which of the specimens at SGO they were referring. Thus, the earliest choice of Johnston is here interpreted as a first-step lectotypification. In order to narrow this designation, the specimen SGO000004088 is here selected as a second-step lectotype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
